Installation Instructions
=========================

Prerequisites:

    - Python 3.6+ with sqlite3 and curses modules
    - A C compiler (optional, for the display-width accelerator)

Quick install:

    ./configure
    make
    make check
    sudo make install

This installs browse-sqlite3 (and a bs3 symlink) to $prefix/bin and
the manpage to $prefix/share/man/man1.

To specify an install prefix:

    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local

To specify a different Python interpreter:

    ./configure --with-python=/usr/bin/python3.12

The C extension (_displaywidth) is built automatically if a C compiler
is available.  If compilation fails, browse-sqlite3 falls back to a
pure-Python implementation with no loss of functionality.

To uninstall:

    sudo make uninstall

Standard targets:

    make            Build the C extension
    make install    Install program, alias, and manpage
    make uninstall  Remove installed files
    make clean      Remove build artifacts
    make distclean  Remove build artifacts and generated Makefile
    make check      Run syntax check
    make dist       Create a release tarball
